sect1.para:
The &Omnetpp;
      IDE provides a "Simulation perspective" to work with simulation related NED, INI and MSG files. To
      switch to the simulation perspective select ``Window | Open Perspective | Simulation''.

In Eclipse, all files are within projects, so first you need a suitable project. The project needs to be
one designated as an &Omnetpp;
Project. (In Eclipse lingo, it should have the &Omnetpp;
Nature.) The easiest way to create such a project is to use a wizard: just choose ``File|New|&Omnetpp;
Project...'' from the menu, specify a project name, and click the ``Finish'' button. If you do not plan
to write simple modules, you may unselect the ``C++ Support'' checkbox which will disable all C++
related features on the project. 

  Creating a new &Omnetpp;
  Project

You may access the online help system from the ``Help | Help Contents'' menu item. The &Omnetpp;
IDE is built on top of Eclipse, so if your are not familiar with Eclipse, we recommend to read
the [[Workbench User Guide]] and the [[C/C++ Development User Guide]] before starting to use &Omnetpp;
specific features.
